race.comment: Tough. OUR INDULGENCE (4) has been within range in his last two and gives every impression the step up to the middle distance will suit. Gets in well with the 3kg claim and is likely to finish hard. ZURICH (6) also lifts from the mile and was tracking well before the latest. Can use the inside gate to advantage and the 4kg claim brings him right into it. Expect more from FINAL APPROACH (2) over the middle distance. Maps well and has the top hoop aboard today. OCCASIONAL GLIMPSE (12) is a leader who will be better for her first go at this distance range. The 3kg claim is handy, but some luck will be required crossing over from the wide gate.
